    {
        "content": "<p>Note that the <code>usize</code>s in <code>RawFormatter</code> are actually pointers, so they generally will not be near <code>usize::MAX</code>. I thought about rewriting it to use pointers, but haven't had the time.</p>",
        "id": 412569927,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1705074366
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yea, as long as no weird combination of machine and configuration decides to allocate memory at the very top of the address available address space everything is fine (not sure if there are any guarantees that this cannot happen though). Thats why I called the example <em>contreived</em> (not so sure if thats the correct word), but maybe a rewrite could still handle this case consistently, i.e., return an error instead of claiming that the operation worked.</p>",
        "id": 412577305,
        "sender_full_name": "Valentin Obst",
        "timestamp": 1705076573
    }
]